## 8. Risk Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|-----------|
| **Workflow flexibility adds too much complexity** | Medium | Medium | MVP launches with 1 mode (Centralized) only; others added in V1.0 based on demand. Test in beta first. |
| **Pricing too high or free tier abused** | Low | Medium | Monitor LTV/CAC monthly; add email validation to free tier; survey churches on $49/mo acceptance. |
| **Planning Center/Breeze launch competing feature** | Low | Medium | Move fast MVP; own "flexible workflows" + "calendar feeds"; differentiate before bigger players move. |
| **Beta churches churn due to feature mismatch** | Low | Low | Weekly feedback loops; prioritize their pain; iterate fast. Workflow flexibility should reduce this. |
| **ChMS integration APIs break or change** | Low | Low | Maintain CSV fallback; never depend solely on API; version-lock dependencies. |
| **Market too niche (only churches)** | Low | Medium | Test nonprofit/school demand in months 3–6; pivot messaging to "volunteer calendar" (broader). |
| **Reminder spam complaints** | Low | Low | Email/SMS toggling per volunteer reduces opt-outs; monitor unsubscribe rates. Target <5% unsubscribe. |
| **You get burned out** | Low | High | 10hr/wk target; use LLM automation heavily; outsource (hiring, contractors) by month 6 if revenue >$500/mo. |

